annotationA: Tyrosine-protein phosphatase non-receptor type 61F; Non-receptor protein tyrosine phosphatase required for maintaining Dock in its non-phosphorylated state
annotationB: Unpaired 1 (Upd1) is a secreted glycol-protein that is able to act at a distance as the primary ligand of the JAK/STAT signaling pathway. Although semi-redundant with upd2 and upd3, Upd1 depletion results in embryonic lethality with an atypical gap gene-like segmentation phenotype
